## (2)(b) LTE Data Rate Calculation

> For an LTE Release 8 FDD system with 20 MHz spectrum, Type 1 frame, normal CP (7 symbols), and 90% effective bandwidth.

**LTE Data:**
- Radio Frame = 10 Sub-frames
- Sub-frame = 2 Time-slots = 1 ms
- Time-slot = 7 OFDM symbols
- Inter-carrier spacing = 15 kHz
- 16 QAM = 4 bits/symbol

---

### (i) Effective Downlink Data Rate

> Using 16 QAM and 2/3 encoding rate. *(10 marks)*

**Step 1: Number of Subcarriers**

<div class="math-left">

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Effective BW} &= 20 \text{ MHz} \times 0.9 = 18 \text{ MHz} \\
\text{Subcarriers} &= \frac{18 \text{ MHz}}{15 \text{ kHz}} = 1200
\end{aligned}$$

</div>

**Step 2: Symbols per Second**

<div class="math-left">

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Symbols per subframe} &= 7 \times 2 = 14 \\
\text{Subframes per second} &= 1000 \\
\text{Total symbols/sec} &= 1200 \times 14 \times 1000 = 16,800,000
\end{aligned}$$

</div>

**Step 3: Apply Modulation and Coding**

<div class="math-left">

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Raw bits/sec} &= 16,800,000 \times 4 = 67.2 \text{ Mbps} \\
\text{With 2/3 coding} &= 67.2 \times \frac{2}{3} = 44.8 \text{ Mbps}
\end{aligned}$$

</div>

> **Effective downlink data rate: 44.8 Mbps**

---

### (ii) Impact of 2x2 MIMO

> What is the impact on system capacity when 2x2 MIMO is used? *(2 marks)*

**2x2 MIMO** provides **2 spatial streams**, effectively **doubling** the capacity:

$$\text{Capacity with MIMO} = 44.8 \times 2 = 89.6 \text{ Mbps}$$

> **With 2x2 MIMO: 89.6 Mbps** (2x increase)
